#: includes/class-bp-activity-filter-admin.php:952
#, fuzzy
msgid "What is BuddyPress Activity Filter?"
msgstr "BuddyPress Aktivitätsfilter"

#: includes/class-bp-activity-filter-admin.php:953
msgid ""
"BuddyPress Activity Filter enhances the default BuddyPress activity stream "
"by providing advanced filtering options. It allows users to filter "
"activities by type, set default filters, and manage which activity types are "
"visible."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bp-activity-filter-admin.php:957
msgid "How do I set a default filter for all activity streams?"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bp-activity-filter-admin.php:958
msgid ""
"Navigate to the Default Filters tab and select your preferred default filter "
"from the dropdown. This filter will be applied automatically when users "
"visit the activity stream."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bp-activity-filter-admin.php:962
msgid "Can I set different default filters for profile pages?"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bp-activity-filter-admin.php:963
msgid ""
"Yes! In the Default Filters tab, you can set a separate default filter "
"specifically for user profile activity streams. This allows for more "
"contextual filtering based on where activities are viewed."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bp-activity-filter-admin.php:967
msgid "How do I hide specific activity types from users?"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bp-activity-filter-admin.php:968
msgid ""
"Use the Hidden Activities tab to select which activity types should be "
"hidden from the filter dropdown. Hidden activities will not appear as filter "
"options for users, though the activities themselves may still be visible in "
"the stream."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bp-activity-filter-admin.php:972
#, fuzzy
msgid "What are Custom Post Type activities?"
msgstr "Aktivieren von Post-Typ-Aktiviten"

#: includes/class-bp-activity-filter-admin.php:973
msgid ""
"When Custom Post Types are published on your site, BuddyPress can create "
"activities for them. The Custom Post Types tab lets you control which CPT "
"activities appear in the filter dropdown and how they are labeled."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bp-activity-filter-admin.php:977
msgid "Can I rename activity type labels in the filter dropdown?"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bp-activity-filter-admin.php:978
msgid ""
"Yes! In the Custom Post Types tab, you can customize the display labels for "
"each post type activity. This helps make filter options more user-friendly "
"and relevant to your community."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bp-activity-filter-admin.php:982
msgid "Why are some activities not showing up in the filter?"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bp-activity-filter-admin.php:983
msgid ""
"Check the Hidden Activities tab to ensure the activity type is not hidden. "
"Also, some activity types may not have a filter option if they are system "
"activities or if they have been disabled by other plugins."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bp-activity-filter-admin.php:987
msgid "Is this plugin compatible with BuddyBoss Platform?"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bp-activity-filter-admin.php:988
msgid ""
"BuddyPress Activity Filter is designed specifically for BuddyPress. "
"BuddyBoss Platform includes its own built-in activity filtering features, so "
"this plugin is not needed and may not be fully compatible with BuddyBoss."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bp-activity-filter-admin.php:992
msgid "How do filters affect activity stream performance?"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bp-activity-filter-admin.php:993
msgid ""
"The plugin is optimized for performance and uses BuddyPress core filtering "
"mechanisms. Filters are applied at the database query level, ensuring "
"efficient loading even with large activity streams."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bp-activity-filter-admin.php:997
